<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05016a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05016a">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05016a"> 16(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> HCE drink</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Probably, although it is not so stated, the Jewish priests gave <font color="green">[their fetish God]</font> Jahveh a drop of something to drink; for it was a thirsty climate, and the old fellow often betrayed a sanguinary violence of temper, which too often springs from intoxication. There is, indeed, a suggestion of this in Judges ix. 13, where we read of &ldquo;<mark>wine which cheereth God and man</mark>.&rdquo; <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [A God in a Box] 117</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
